race.comment: SOCIABLE (1) switched to the Maher yard and looked a run short placing here first-up. Draws inside today and is still well shy of his Victorian best. Proven second-up, and this is a winnable assignment. ALL THE WAY MAE (6) impressed her brief initial preparation and has no luck here the latest at a short quote. Draws inside with Brock Ryan booked and naturally improved, a bold run is likely. MISSIE LEE (3) deserved her Maiden win here second up over the trip. She's promising and maps well. She won't have to improve much to be in the finish. LUSKINTYRE (7) has an inside gate and brings a Maiden win from Newcastle. She is still shy of her best and deserves consideration. GHIELMI (2) has been freshened and has the blinkers on again. He will skip across and control the race, and his best form would see him very competitive.
